proxs3 (0.2.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix cache_dir config being ignored - plugin now queries daemon for
    the actual cache path instead of hardcoding /var/cache/proxs3 (#1)
  * Remove CacheDirectory= from systemd unit (was breaking symlinks)
  * Fix build on Debian 12 Bookworm build environments (#2)
  * Require PVE 9+ at runtime (plugin API targets PVE 9)
  * Add /v1/config API endpoint
  * Comprehensive test suite (95 tests) with S3 client mock interface

 -- Dave Kempe <dave@sol1.com.au>  Sun, 09 Mar 2026 10:00:00 +0000

proxs3 (0.2.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Multipart upload support for files >5GB (AWS SDK upload manager)
  * Prevent uploading partial writes (fileInUse /proc/fd check, skip .tmp files)
  * Per-storage cache-max-age property for automatic local cache eviction
  * Cache metadata in .meta/ subdirectory (fixes watcher sidecar loop)
  * activate_volume downloads S3 objects on demand
  * Graceful degradation when S3 is unreachable (timeouts, stale cache serving)
  * Endpoint config sanitisation (strip protocol prefix and trailing slash)
  * Credentials optional for public buckets

 -- Dave Kempe <dave@sol1.com.au>  Sun, 08 Mar 2026 17:00:00 +0000

